{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011u6yni2omBVGpbjBwMXGb3","type":"tool_result","content":"    90→func (s *ClocheServer) RunWorkflow(ctx context.Context, req *pb.RunWorkflowRequest) (*pb.RunWorkflowResponse, error) {\n    91→\t// Check for resume mode via gRPC metadata\n    92→\tif resumeRunID := resumeRunIDFromContext(ctx); resumeRunID != \"\" {\n    93→\t\treturn s.resumeRun(ctx, resumeRunID, resumeStepFromContext(ctx))\n    94→\t}\n    95→\n    96→\t// Check if this is a host workflow (has host {} block).\n    97→\tif hostWFs, err := host.FindHostWorkflows(req.ProjectDir); err == nil {\n    98→\t\tif _, isHost := hostWFs[req.WorkflowName]; isHost {\n    99→\t\t\treturn s.runHostWorkflow(ctx, req)\n   100→\t\t}\n   101→\t}\n   102→\n   103→\tif s.container == nil {\n   104→\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"no container runtime configured\")\n   105→\t}\n   106→\n   107→\t// Generate a unique run ID, retrying on collision\n   108→\tvar runID string\n   109→\tfor attempts := 0; attempts < 10; attempts++ {\n   110→\t\trunID = domain.GenerateRunID(req.WorkflowName)\n   111→\t\texisting, err := s.store.GetRun(ctx, runID)\n   112→\t\tif err != nil {\n   113→\t\t\tbreak // ID is free\n   114→\t\t}\n   115→\t\t// Reuse if completed more than 1 hour ago\n   116→\t\tif !existing.CompletedAt.IsZero() && time.Since(existing.CompletedAt) > time.Hour {\n   117→\t\t\t_ = s.store.DeleteRun(ctx, runID)\n   118→\t\t\tbreak\n   119→\t\t}\n   120→\t}\n   121→\n   122→\t// Write prompt to .cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt (run-specific to avoid conflicts)\n   123→\tif req.Prompt != \"\" {\n   124→\t\tclocheDir := filepath.Join(req.ProjectDir, \".cloche\", runID)\n   125→\t\tif err := os.MkdirAll(clocheDir, 0755); err != nil {\n   126→\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"creating .cloche dir: %w\", err)\n   127→\t\t}\n   128→\t\tif err := os.WriteFile(filepath.Join(clocheDir, \"prompt.txt\"), []byte(req.Prompt), 0644); err != nil {\n   129→\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"writing prompt: %w\", err)\n   130→\t\t}\n   131→\t}\n   132→\trun := domain.NewRun(runID, req.WorkflowName)\n   133→\trun.ProjectDir = req.ProjectDir\n   134→\trun.Title = req.Title\n   135→\trun.TaskID = req.IssueId\n   136→\tif err := s.store.CreateRun(ctx, run); err != nil {\n   137→\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"creating run: %w\", err)\n   138→\t}\n   139→\n   140→\t// Resolve image: request-level override, then server default\n   141→\timage := req.Image\n   142→\tif image == \"\" {\n   143→\t\timage = s.defaultImage\n   144→\t}\n   145→\n   146→\t// Launch container start + tracking in background so the RPC returns immediately.\n   147→\t// The run stays in \"pending\" state until the container is up.\n   148→\tgo s.launchAndTrack(runID, image, req.KeepContainer, req)\n   149→\n   150→\treturn &pb.RunWorkflowResponse{RunId: runID}, nil\n   151→}\n   152→\n   153→// runHostWorkflow dispatches a host workflow via the host runner, returning\n   154→// immediately while the workflow runs in a background goroutine."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01CHsGfHFbwJREmYZ4LmDQS2","session_id":"20d5adfa-ca6e-4c90-b84e-e05e5aa65257","uuid":"c25e4374-3df9-4241-8c50-a64966acc8fd","timestamp":"2026-03-17T14:08:21.390Z"}
{"type":"system","subtype":"task_notification","task_id":"a244e39b1a54df44c","tool_use_id":"toolu_01CHsGfHFbwJREmYZ4LmDQS2","status":"completed","output_file":"","summary":"Explore evolution and population code","usage":{"total_tokens":73850,"tool_uses":41,"duration_ms":92887},"uuid":"b0f6be23-5dec-447f-b5b8-6472416181e5","session_id":"20d5adfa-ca6e-4c90-b84e-e05e5aa65257"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CHsGfHFbwJREmYZ4LmDQS2","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Let me compile my final report:\n\n## Comprehensive Codebase Exploration Report\n\n### 1. VERSION\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/version/VERSION`\n- **Current Version:** `1.14.1`\n\n### 2. EVOLUTION SYSTEM OVERVIEW\n\nThe evolution system is a self-improving workflow pipeline that analyzes workflow execution, extracts lessons, and evolves prompts and workflows automatically.\n\n#### Core Evolution Pipeline Architecture:\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/evolution/`\n\n**Orchestrator** (`orchestrator.go`):\n- **Type:** `Orchestrator` struct with config-based wiring\n- **Key Capabilities:**\n  - Coordinates all evolution pipeline stages\n  - Executes full evolution runs on-demand\n  - Manages lesson deduplication and knowledge base updates\n- **Main Method:** `Run(ctx, triggerRunID, evoStore, capStore) (*EvolutionResult, error)`\n- **Config:** `OrchestratorConfig` with fields:\n  - `ProjectDir`: string\n  - `WorkflowName`: string\n  - `LLM`: LLMClient interface\n  - `MinConfidence`: string (\"low\", \"medium\", \"high\")\n  - `MaxPromptBullets`: int\n\n**Pipeline Stages:**\n\n1. **Collector** (`collector.go`)\n   - Gathers runs, captures, knowledge base, prompts, and workflow state\n   - Reads workflow DSL from `.cloche/<workflow-name>.cloche`\n   - Extracts prompt files referenced via `file()` in workflow\n   - Reads JSONL knowledge base from `.cloche/evolution/knowledge/<workflow>.jsonl`\n   - Type: `Collector` struct with `ProjectDir` and `WorkflowName`\n\n2. **Classifier** (`classifier.go`)\n   - Categorizes runs into: `bug`, `feedback`, `feature`, `enhancement`, `chore`\n   - Uses LLM to classify the triggering run\n   - Returns a single classification string\n\n3. **Reflector** (`reflector.go`)\n   - Examines execution traces and extracts structured lessons\n   - Filters by minimum confidence level\n   - Deduplicates against knowledge base\n   - Returns `[]Lesson` where each Lesson has:\n     - `ID`: unique identifier\n     - `Category`: \"prompt_improvement\" or \"new_step\"\n     - `StepType`: \"script\" or \"agent\" (for new_step)\n     - `Target`: prompt file path (for prompt_improvement)\n     - `Insight`: what pattern was observed\n     - `SuggestedAction`: concrete change to make\n     - `Evidence`: list of run IDs supporting the lesson\n     - `Confidence`: \"high\", \"medium\", or \"low\"\n\n4. **Curator** (`curator.go`)\n   - Merges lessons into prompt files using ACE (Agentic Context Engineering)\n   - Detects if lesson already present in prompt (case-insensitive)\n   - Validates LLM output for conversational meta-text\n   - Falls back to direct append if LLM returns conversational text\n   - Creates snapshots before modifications for rollback capability\n   - Performs post-write sanity checks to detect corruption\n\n5. **ScriptGenerator** (`scriptgen.go`)\n   - Generates shell scripts for new validation steps\n   - Validates script paths (must be in `scripts/` or `.cloche/scripts/`)\n   - Writes scripts as non-executable (workflow engine handles execution)\n   - Validates shebang line presence\n   - Type: `ScriptGenerator` struct with `LLM` field\n\n6. **AuditLogger** (`audit.go`)\n   - Logs evolution results to `.cloche/evolution/log.jsonl` (JSONL format)\n   - Creates snapshots of files before modification\n   - Manages knowledge base JSONL files\n   - Handles deduplication and pruning with `MaxPromptBullets`\n   - Methods:\n     - `Log(result)`: append to log\n     - `Snapshot(relativePath)`: create backup\n     - `Restore(relativePath, snapName)`: rollback\n     - `UpdateKnowledge(workflowName, lessons)`: merge into JSONL KB\n     - `KnowledgePath(workflowName)`: get KB file path\n\n### 3. TRIGGER SYSTEM\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/evolution/trigger.go`\n\n**Trigger Type:**\n- Debounces evolution pipeline runs per project+workflow key\n- Configurable debounce seconds (defaults to 30)\n- Type: `Trigger` struct with `TriggerConfig`:\n  - `DebounceSeconds`: int\n  - `RunFunc`: callback function `func(projectDir, workflowName, runID string)`\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- `Fire(projectDir, workflowName, runID)`: Schedule or reschedule evolution run\n- `Stop()`: Cancel all pending timers\n\n### 4. DAEMON WIRING\n\n**File:** `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go`\n\n**initEvolution Function** (lines 160-197):\n```\nCreates evolution trigger from global + project config\n- Loads per-project config from <projectDir>/.cloche/config.toml\n- Reads evolution settings: Enabled, DebounceSeconds, MinConfidence, MaxPromptBullets\n- Creates CommandLLMClient wrapping the configured LLM command\n- Returns initialized evolution.Trigger or nil if disabled\n- Trigger is attached to gRPC server via SetEvolution()\n```\n\n**Config Structure:** `EvolutionConfig` in `/workspace/internal/config/config.go`\n- `Enabled`: bool (default: true)\n- `DebounceSeconds`: int (default: 30)\n- `MinConfidence`: string (default: \"medium\")\n- `MaxPromptBullets`: int (default: 50) - max lessons to keep in KB\n\n### 5. GRPC SERVER INTEGRATION\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`\n\n**ClocheServer Fields:**\n- `evolution`: *evolution.Trigger\n- `runIDs`: map[string]string (run_id -> container_id)\n- `loops`: map[string]*host.Loop (project_dir -> orchestration loop)\n\n**launchAndTrack** (lines 320-368):\n1. Ensures container image is built (if EnsureImage available)\n2. Starts container with ContainerConfig\n3. Stores run_id -> container_id mapping\n4. Updates run state to \"running\", captures BaseSHA, ContainerID\n5. Calls trackRun() to monitor execution\n\n**trackRun** (lines 370-582):\n1. Registers run in log broadcaster for live-streaming\n2. Attaches to container output, parses JSON-line status messages\n3. Processes message types:\n   - `MsgLog`: publishes to logBroadcast (fast path)\n   - `MsgStepStarted`: records step start, saves capture\n   - `MsgStepCompleted`: records step result, saves capture\n   - `MsgRunTitle`: updates run title\n   - `MsgError`: captured for error message\n   - `MsgRunCompleted`: captured for final result\n4. Waits for container exit\n5. Extracts step output files to `.cloche/<run-id>/output/`\n6. Indexes log files in log store\n7. Extracts results to git branch `cloche/<run-id>` using docker.ExtractResults()\n8. Finalizes run state based on reportedResult and exitCode\n9. **Fires evolution trigger** if configured (line 548: `s.evolution.Fire(projectDir, workflowName, runID)`)\n10. Handles container retention policy (keep on failure, delete unless --keep-container)\n11. Cleans up run ID mapping\n\n**Key Integration Points:**\n- `SetEvolution(trigger *evolution.Trigger)`: Attach evolution trigger\n- `SetLogStore(ls ports.LogStore)`: Attach log store\n- `SetLogBroadcaster(b *logstream.Broadcaster)`: Attach broadcaster\n- `SetShutdownFunc(fn func())`: Register shutdown callback\n\n### 6. STORE INTERFACES\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go`\n\n**RunStore Interface:**\n- `CreateRun`, `GetRun`, `UpdateRun`, `DeleteRun`\n- `ListRuns`, `ListRunsByProject`, `ListRunsFiltered`, `ListProjects`\n- `ListChildRuns`\n\n**CaptureStore Interface:**\n- `SaveCapture(ctx, runID, stepExecution)`: Save step execution data\n- `GetCaptures(ctx, runID) -> []*StepExecution`\n\n**EvolutionStore Interface:**\n- `SaveEvolution(ctx, entry)`: Persist evolution result\n- `GetLastEvolution(ctx, projectDir, workflowName)`: Get most recent evolution\n- `ListRunsSince(ctx, projectDir, workflowName, sinceRunID)`: Get runs since evolution\n\n**EvolutionEntry:**\n- `ID`, `ProjectDir`, `WorkflowName`, `TriggerRunID`\n- `CreatedAt`, `Classification`, `ChangesJSON`, `KnowledgeDelta`\n\n### 7. DOMAIN TYPES\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`\n\n**Run Struct:**\n- `ID`, `WorkflowName`, `State` (RunState enum)\n- `ActiveSteps`: []string\n- `StepExecutions`: []*StepExecution\n- `StartedAt`, `CompletedAt`: time.Time\n- `ProjectDir`, `ErrorMessage`, `ContainerID`, `BaseSHA`\n- `ContainerKept`, `Title`, `IsHost`, `ParentRunID`, `TaskID`\n\n**StepExecution:**\n- `StepName`, `Result`, `StartedAt`, `CompletedAt`, `Logs`, `GitRef`\n\n**RunState:** string constants\n- `RunStatePending`, `RunStateRunning`, `RunStateSucceeded`, `RunStateFailed`, `RunStateCancelled`\n\n### 8. EVOLUTION TYPES\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/evolution/types.go`\n\n**CollectedData:**\n- `Runs`: []*domain.Run\n- `Captures`: map[string][]*domain.StepExecution (run_id -> executions)\n- `KnowledgeBase`: string (JSONL content)\n- `CurrentPrompts`: map[string]string (relative path -> content)\n- `CurrentWorkflow`, `WorkflowPath`, `ProjectDir`, `WorkflowName`\n\n**Lesson:**\n- All fields in JSON format: `id`, `category`, `step_type`, `target`, `insight`, `suggested_action`, `evidence`, `confidence`\n\n**EvolutionResult:**\n- `ID`, `ProjectDir`, `WorkflowName`, `TriggerRunID`, `Timestamp`\n- `Classification`, `Changes`, `KnowledgeDelta`\n\n**Change:**\n- `Type`: \"prompt_update\", \"add_step\", \"add_script\", \"prompt_update_rollback\"\n- `File`: relative path\n- `Reason`: insight/description\n- `Snapshot`: snapshot filename for rollback\n\n### 9. LLM CLIENT\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/evolution/llmclient.go`\n\n**LLMClient Interface:**\n- `Complete(ctx, systemPrompt, userPrompt) (string, error)`\n\n**CommandLLMClient:**\n- `Command`: string (path to LLM executable)\n- `Args`: []string (additional args)\n- Invokes LLM with:\n  - `-p` flag (print/non-interactive mode)\n  - `--system-prompt <system>` (if non-empty)\n  - `--output-format text`\n  - User prompt via stdin\n\n### 10. EVOLUTION PACKAGE FILES\n\nAll in `/workspace/internal/evolution/`:\n- `types.go` (57 lines): Type definitions\n- `trigger.go` (64 lines): Debounce trigger\n- `trigger_test.go`: Tests for trigger\n- `collector.go` (92 lines): Data collection\n- `classifier.go` (51 lines): Run classification\n- `reflector.go` (130 lines): Lesson extraction\n- `curator.go` (195 lines): Prompt curation\n- `audit.go` (174 lines): Logging and snapshots\n- `scriptgen.go` (114 lines): Script generation\n- `llmclient.go` (59 lines): LLM command wrapper\n- `orchestrator.go` (249 lines): Pipeline coordination\n- `evolution_test.go` (1199 lines): Comprehensive unit tests\n- `corruption_test.go` (33732 bytes): Corruption/resilience tests\n- `scriptgen_test.go`: Script generation tests\n- Total: ~3550 lines of Go code\n\n### 11. TESTING\n\n**Unit Tests:** `/workspace/internal/evolution/evolution_test.go`\n- Tests for each pipeline stage (Collector, Classifier, Reflector, Curator, ScriptGenerator)\n- Tests for AuditLogger (JSONL logging, snapshots, knowledge base)\n- Tests for code fence stripping, conversational response detection\n- Tests for lesson deduplication and already-applied lesson filtering\n- End-to-end orchestrator tests including new step addition\n- Tests for duplicate step prevention and workflow graph validation\n\n**Integration Tests:** `/workspace/test/integration/evolution_test.go`\n- Full pipeline integration test\n- Project setup and execution verification\n\n### 12. KEY INTEGRATION FLOW\n\n1. **Run Completion** → `trackRun()` in grpc/server.go\n2. **Fire Evolution Trigger** → `s.evolution.Fire(projectDir, workflowName, runID)` (line 548)\n3. **Debounce Wait** → After configured seconds, run callback\n4. **Orchestrator.Run()** → Full pipeline:\n   - Collect → Classify → Reflect → (filter low-confidence, dedup against KB)\n   - For each lesson:\n     - If `prompt_improvement`: Curator.Apply()\n     - If `new_step`: Generate script, add to workflow, wire into graph\n   - Audit.UpdateKnowledge() → Persist lessons to JSONL KB\n   - Audit.Log() → Record evolution result\n5. **Result Persistence** → SaveEvolution() to database\n\n### 13. FILES NOT YET IMPLEMENTED\n\n**NOT FOUND** in current codebase:\n- `PopulationConfig` - not yet defined\n- `Population` struct/interface - not yet defined\n- `Selector` interface - not yet defined\n- `SelectCandidate` - not yet defined\n- `ScoreAndPromote` - not yet defined\n- GEPA (Genetic Evolutionary Prompt Advancement) - not yet implemented\n\nThese will be future enhancements for population-based multi-candidate selection and fitness-based promotion.\n\n---\n\n**Absolute File Paths for Reference:**\n- `/workspace/internal/version/VERSION` - Current version 1.14.1\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go` - Daemon entry, `initEvolution()` at line 160\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/orchestrator.go` - Main orchestrator with `Run()` method\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/trigger.go` - Event trigger and debouncer\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` - gRPC server with `launchAndTrack()` and `trackRun()`\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/*.go` - All evolution pipeline stages (14 files, ~3550 lines)\n- `/workspace/internal/config/config.go` - EvolutionConfig structure with 4 fields\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` - RunStore, CaptureStore, EvolutionStore interfaces\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` - Run and StepExecution domain types"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a244e39b1a54df44c (use SendMessage with to: 'a244e39b1a54df44c' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 77551\ntool_uses: 41\nduration_ms: 92890</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"20d5adfa-ca6e-4c90-b84e-e05e5aa65257","uuid":"71aeb5b9-978e-4f1b-ae93-f33bc78af54a","timestamp":"2026-03-17T14:08:58.177Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase thoroughly to understand:\n\n1. The evolution system - find all files related to evolution, population, GEPA, fitness, selection, candidates, promotion\n2. The daemon wiring in cmd/cloched/main.go - especially initEvolution() function\n3. The gRPC server in internal/adapters/grpc/server.go - especially launchAndTrack() and trackRun() functions\n4. Population types, 