{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_018Tfptc8ha3GXuQvKxQ1424","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a good understanding. Let me look at how the workflow DSL references prompt files, so I know what path format to use for population candidates.\n\nPrompts are stored like `.cloche/prompts/implement.md` and referenced in workflows as `file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")` or `file(\"prompts/implement.md\")`.\n\nNow let me design the population system:\n\n1. **PopulationConfig** - in config.go, nested under EvolutionConfig\n   - `Enabled bool`\n   - `Size int` (number of candidates to maintain)\n   - `PromotionThreshold float64` (fitness threshold for promotion)\n\n\n2. **Population** - manages candidate prompts for a workflow, storing them as JSONL files in `.cloche/evolution/population/<workflow>/` with each candidate tracking ID, content, fitness, generation, and run count.\n3. **Selector** - an interface for selecting candidates from the population.\n4. **Population.SelectCandidate()** and **Population.ScoreAndPromote()** - methods to pick the best candidate and record fitness scores with promotion logic.\n\nLet me check what the existing tests look like to understand the testing patterns.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3615,"cache_read_input_tokens":43881,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3615},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"20d5adfa-ca6e-4c90-b84e-e05e5aa65257","uuid":"370b5af8-ab28-4cb7-aa98-181999cad64a"}
