{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01EkrnHWScuLPCTphjwVa6g2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The test fails because when a candidate is promoted (its content is written to the prompt path), restoring the snapshot won't work since the assignment is already deleted by ScoreAndPromote. Also the issue is that after promotion, the restore still tries to restore the original, but the promoted content was already written.\n\nThe issue is in the end-to-end test: after ScoreAndPromote promotes a candidate (writing its content to the prompt), we try to restore the snapshot. But the promoted content should stay. Let me fix the test logic - after promotion, we should NOT restore the snapshot, and the `originalPrompt` variable should be updated to the promoted content for subsequent comparisons.\n\n\nActually, I'm realizing ScoreAndPromote deletes the assignment from the map before loading candidates, so GetAssignment returns nil afterward. But the test restores using the assignment variable captured from ApplyCandidate, not from GetAssignment, so the restore should actually work.\n\nThe real problem is that when a candidate gets promoted, ScoreAndPromote writes its content to the prompt path, then RestoreSnapshot overwrites it back to the original. But the test assertion is checking for the original prompt content and finding \"Gamma prompt: focus on simplicity\" instead, which means either the snapshot wasn't captured correctly or the restore didn't work as expected.\n\nI think what's happening is that in the second iteration, the prompt file still contains candidate content from the previous promotion, so when ApplyCandidate creates a new snapshot, it's capturing that modified content instead of the true original. This means RestoreSnapshot restores to the wrong baseline. I see the real problem now—when promotion happens, the test skips the RestoreSnapshot call, leaving the promoted content in place. Then on the next iteration, ApplyCandidate snapshots that promoted content instead of the original, so subsequent restores go back to the wrong state. I need to update the original prompt reference whenever promotion occurs so the snapshots stay consistent.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1196,"cache_read_input_tokens":62664,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1196},"output_tokens":10,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"20d5adfa-ca6e-4c90-b84e-e05e5aa65257","uuid":"7040e327-2692-4990-a4ed-038c9a69599f"}
